** The Company **   
  
Our client is a successful and well establish engineering consultancy
specialising in heavy industry and bulk export and are conveniently based in
Brisbane CBD.  
  
They have been trading for almost 10 years and have benefited from year-on-
year growth and continued success. They work on high profile, technically
challenging projects for a range of impressive clients  
  
They possess the agility of a small independent business and can make prompt
decisions and pivot quickly to capitalise on market opportunities.
Furthermore, they offer a personalised and friendly work environment where
everyone’s contribution is recognised.  
  
** Graduate and Intermediate Engineers with local experience are encouraged to apply. **   
  
** The Role **   
As a Structural Engineer, you will be expected to deliver quality engineering
outcomes for clients and complement the mechanical engineering function of the
business.  

  * Prepare design calculations and reports 
  * Produce technical specifications 
  * Develop concepts, pre-feasibility, feasibility, and detailed design tasks 
  * Support the drafting function, as required 
  * Prepare tender submissions 
  * Use and maintain the internal job management and reporting systems 
  * Budget and schedule management of your team 
  * Liaise with clients, as required 
While this role is predominantly office based, you will be required to travel
from time to time to attend site visits, inspections and/or audits as well as
attend external client meetings.  
  
** You **   

  * Tertiary qualification in Structural Engineering 
  * Experience working in a ** local ** consultancy ( ** applicants must have Australian or New Zealand experience) **
  * Experience working on ** industrial projects ** – mining, ports, heavy industry etc 
  * High level structural design abilities 
  * Competency in industry standard design software e.g. ** SPACE GASS, STRAND7 **
  * Attention to detail 
  * Excellent communication skills – both verbal and written 
** The Reward **   
If successful, you will be given the opportunity to join a hugely successful
team of clever and down to earth engineers and technical professionals.  
